<TITLE>Career Transitions offers winter skills classes</TITLE>
<TEXT>
Enrollment is now open for “Ready 2 Work” classes at Career Transitions in Belgrade. Through specialized training, students are rewarded with new skills, certificates, and job readiness training beneficial in finding employment. The following classes are now open for enrollment: Certified Nurse Assistant, First Aid/ Advanced CPR, Computer Basics for Seniors, Introduction to Computers, Microsoft Word #1 and #2, Excel, Basic Bookkeeping, QuickBooks, Mastering Payroll, and Class A   Commercial Driver’s License training. 
   
Career Transitions invites students to explore and advance careers in bookkeeping through Ready 2 Work classes. “Bookkeeping Basics,” “Introduction to QuickBooks” and “Mastering Payroll” are offered sequentially during the winter semester. Through these classes students acquire skills essential to personal finance and/or small business management. Beginning students are invited to enroll in a two night class: “Bookkeeping Basics” offered on Tuesday, Feb. 16 and Thursday Feb. 21. This class will provides sufficient background for the beginning student to then take the QuickBooks class. “Introduction to QuickBooks” is held Feb. 23 – March 23. This 14 hour class meets Tuesday nights and Thursday nights. Students will learn how to install, set up and work in all areas of QuickBooks for a small business. “Mastering Payroll with QuickBooks” is a two night class held March 28 and March 30 on Tuesday and Thursday nights. This 4 hour class introduces the experienced bookkeeper to the basics of payroll and its practical application. 
   
× 
 
   
Certified Nursing Assistant Training begins March 6. Participating students will receive comprehensive CNA training in this nine week, 86 hour class. The class meets Monday and Wednesday evenings from 5:30 – 8:30 p.m. and every other Saturday during the day. 
   
The class includes coursework, hands on activities, residential experience and job readiness training. The book “Nursing Assistant Care: The Basics” is utilized as a reference. The registration fee of $775 includes the textbook, instruction, lab experience, practice tests, final certification test, job readiness and soft skills training. The class culminates in final knowledge and skills tests to qualify for Montana certification. 
   
Students will be trained by experienced nurses of Spring Creek Inn, a memory care community. The teachers are certified to teach CNA programs with the State of Montana. In addition to class time, students may participate in one on one tutorials as needed. 
   
Space in this class is limited to 10 students. Registration with tuition payment will hold the student’s place. A TB test and immunization for Tetanus/Diphtheria is also required.
